title: Love Island Australia stars' complete transformations revealed
text:
The cast of Love Island Australia are the hottest reality stars on TV right now.

And in recent years, the male and female contestants have gone to great lengths to transform themselves in preparation for their moment in the spotlight.

From boob jobs and lip filler to full sleeve tattoos, some of them are completely unrecognisable in throwback photos taken just few years ago.

Love Island Australia stars like you've NEVER seen them before! Throwback photos reveal what the cast looked like before their glamorous TV transformations

Tasmanian influencer Jessie Wynter has made no secret of the fact she previously underwent a breast enlargement.

During the first few minutes of Monday's episode, the busty 23-year-old joked about how expensive the surgery had been.

Since 2013, Jessie has also swapped her brunette hair in favour of a blonde bombshell look, and has also adopted a more glamorous makeup palette.

Loud and proud! Jessie Wynter has made no secret of the fact she previously underwent a breast enlargement. Pictured left: Jessie in 2013, and right: on Love Island Australia

Glow up! Since 2013, Jessie has also swapped her brunette hair in favour of a blonde bombshell look, and has also adopted a more glamorous makeup palette

Older photos of Vanessa Sierra also reveal how she has transformed her appearance.

In throwback snaps from her teenage years, the 24-year-old businesswoman looks completely different and far less glamorous than today.

Several photos show her with a larger nose and noticeably thinner lips, which suggests she may have undergone cosmetic enhancements.

Wow! In photos from her teenage years, Vanessa Sierra looks completely different and far less glamorous than today. Pictured left: as a teenager, and right: in a recent modelling photo

Did she go under the knife? Several photos show Vanessa with a larger nose and noticeably thinner lips (left), which suggests she may have undergone cosmetic enhancements

Cassie Lansdell is another Love Island Australia contestant who was experimented with her look.

Not only has the executive assistant, 27, ditched her brown hair to go blonde, but her lips have also increased in size over the past few years.

Furthermore, she has been steadily growing her tattoo collection since 2013.

Edgy! Cassie Lansdell has also experimented with her look over the years, swapping her brown hair for blonde and also getting lip filler. Pictured left: in 2013, and right: in 2019

Work of art! She has also been steadily growing her tattoo collection since 2013 (left)

Anna McEvoy is set to make her Love Island debut as an intruder on Tuesday night.

And she'll certainly fit in, having significantly upped the glamour over the past few years.

'So excited to hopefully find love, cross your fingers and toes for me,' she said on Monday.

Glam! Anna McEvoy is set to make her Love Island debut as an intruder on Tuesday - and she'll certainly fit in, having significantly upped the glamour over the past few years. Pictured left: in 2013, and right: in 2019

Some of the Love Island men have changed things up in recent years too.

Eoghan Murphy hasn't always been quite so rugged, opting for a clean shaven style with shorter hair in 2016.

Meanwhile, Matthew Zukowski has ditched his glasses and trimmed his floppy boyband-style hair from 2013, and now slicks it back.

Much better! Eoghan Murphy hasn't always been quite so rugged, opting for a clean shaven style with shorter hair in 2016 (left). Pictured right: in 2019
